          __Thoracic cavity__ or chest cavity is the more superior subdivision of the anterior cavity, and it is bound laterally by the ribs (covered by costal pleura) and the diaphragm caudally (covered by diaphragmatic pleura). The diaphragm forms the floor of the thoracic cavity and separates it from the more inferior abdominopelvic cavity. The viscera of the thoracic cavity includes the __heart, lungs, trachea, esophagus, large blood vessels, and nerves__. The Thoracic Cavity is partitioned into two pleural cavities, one surrounding each lung and the pericardial surrounding the heart. The area between two lungs is know as the __mediastinum__.


